Sentencas: A dip-coating method to fabricate anode-supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells has been successfully developed.
Titulo: Dip-coating and co-sintering technologies for fabricating tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The length, outside diameter, and thickness of the single cell are 10.8 cm, 1.0 cm, and 0.6 mm, respectively.
Titulo: Dip-coating and co-sintering technologies for fabricating tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area of the cathode is 15-16 cm(2) (cathode length = 4.8 cm).
Titulo: Dip-coating and co-sintering technologies for fabricating tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell consists of a Ni-YSZ anode support tube, a Ni-ScSZ anode functional layer, a ScSZ electrolyte film, a LSM-ScSZ cathode functional layer, and a LSM cathode current collecting layer.
Titulo: Dip-coating and co-sintering technologies for fabricating tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A preliminary examination of the single tubular cell has been carried out and an acceptable performance was obtained.
Titulo: Dip-coating and co-sintering technologies for fabricating tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density was, respectively, 325, 276, 208, and 168 mW cm(-2) at 850, 800, 750, and 700 A degrees C, when operating with humidified hydrogen.
Titulo: Dip-coating and co-sintering technologies for fabricating tubular solid oxide fuel cells
